modules.description: The module offers operations for managing key-value maps, including adding, removing, updating, and querying bindings, along with iteration and membership checks. It works with map types that support custom key equality and merging strategies, enabling precise control over data composition. Use cases include configuration management, data aggregation, and dynamic rule application where bindings need to be combined or filtered based on specific logic.

Writes ICS format duration values into a buffer using a time span. Converts calendar properties to ICS key strings for event metadata. Designed for generating calendar file content with precise time and property formatting.

Parses and generates iCalendar files by converting between structured event data and RFC5545-compliant text. Works with event records containing start and end times, recurrence rules, and alarm details. Used to generate calendar exports from application data and to import event schedules into a system's internal representation.

manages key-value mappings with customizable equality and merging, enabling dynamic data composition and query operations; supports time-based formatting for calendar properties, allowing precise generation of ICS duration values and event metadata; operations include adding, removing, and iterating over bindings, as well as converting time spans to ICS-compatible strings; examples include building event configurations with custom rules and exporting time-based data in standardized calendar formats.
